        "0": {
            "uid": 0,
            "comment": "ARC_STATE — Arc 4: Primal Grounding",
            "key": [],
            "keysecondary": [],
            "selectiveLogic": 0,
            "content": "**Dramatic Situation:** \nIt is mid-December 2024. The five-year cycle of La Grande Caccia (The Great Hunt) has arrived at the Dead Zone in Blackwood Forest, replacing the Winter Hunt. Modern technology, cell phones, and DCC surveillance die at the perimeter. The continental wolf gathering features the Grand Festival (Dec 14-15) with giant bonfires, mead, drums, and ritual dances. Wulfnic publicly overrules Erik's orders by invoking ancient Fenris law to permit {{user}} to run as the White Moon Dominant Omega. {{user}} possesses total freedom of action in the wilderness (partnering, evading, or confronting the hunt), while Erik seethes in protective, trauma-driven rage.\n\n**Tonal Mandate (binding behavioral directive — applies to every response in this arc):**\n- STRIP AWAY all modern technology, cell phones, and corporate aesthetics; enforce acoustic vacuum technology death.\n- ENFORCE pure, feral LSE biological mechanics: heavy scent communication, war paint rituals, instinctual hierarchy, and the physical weight of the pack.\n- HIGHLIGHT Wulfnic's absolute ceremonial authority over Erik as host of La Grande Caccia and living saga of Fenris law.\n- RESPECT {{user}}'s total agency during La Grande Caccia: allow {{user}} to choose whether to run alongside a partner, hide and evade all hunters, or embrace the primal instincts of the White Moon.\n- DEPICT Erik's intense overprotection, trauma from Nixara's Caccia, and seething rage at Wulfnic stripping away his corporate control.",
            "position": 1,
            "order": 100,
            "depth": 4,
            "role": 0,
